AB  - A dual cost function embodying biased technical change is estimated for the postwar primary metals industry. The identifying restriction of constant rates of factor augmentation is used to derive significant estimates of rates of biased technical change which are consistent with the induced innovation hypothesis. Also, the bias in elasticity estimates which results from ignoring biased technical change is shown to be serious.
